# Clayworth graph: Sabidussi coset graph on 4032 vertices

The **Clayworth graph** (4032 vertices, cubic, genus 505) is `Sab(G₂(2), C₃)`.
`|G₂(2)| = 12096`, `|C₃| = 3`, `12096/3 = 4032` vertices.

The graph is defined via O(1) neighbor lookup from precomputed adjacency data.
Two generators of G₂(2) (orders 7 and 6) are shown to preserve adjacency,
and BFS witness words prove transitivity.

* **Main result**: `clayworthSabidussiIso` — the Clayworth graph is a Sabidussi
  coset graph
* [Visualization](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/RaggedR/symmetric-graphs/main/lean/named_graphs/clayworth-4032v.jpg)

## References

* Robin Langer, *Symmetric Graphs and their Quotients*, arXiv:1306.4798
